com.apriori.concurrent

Interface ContextPropagator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of context value that is propagated

    public interface ContextPropagator<T>
    An object that helps propagate context from one thread to another. The general usage pattern of this interface is as follows: 
     ContextPropagator<T> propagator;
 // capture state from one thread
 T state = propagator.capture();
 
 // then install that state in a different thread
 T prevVal = propagator.install(state);
 try {
    doSomeWorkInOtherThread();
 } finally {
   propagator.restore(prevVal);
 }

      • create

        static <T> ContextPropagator<T> create(Supplier<? extends T> capturer,
                                       Consumer<? super T> installer)
        Creates a ContextPropagator whose pieces are defined using functional interfaces. This allows lambda expressions to be used to define the three methods of this interface.

        This override allows callers to just provide a getter (the capture step) and a setter (the restore step). The install step of the returned propagator will just use both of those.

        Parameters:
        capturer - captures context of the calling thread
        installer - installs a context value into the calling thread
        Returns:
        a propagator that uses the given objects to propagate context

      • create

        static <T> ContextPropagator<T> create(Supplier<? extends T> capturer,
                                       Function<? super T,? extends T> installer)
        Creates a ContextPropagator whose pieces are defined using functional interfaces. This allows lambda expressions to be used to define the three methods of this interface.

        This override allows callers to just provide the capture piece and the install piece. The restore step of the returned propagator will just invoke the install logic and discard its return value.

        Parameters:
        capturer - captures context of the calling thread
        installer - installs a context value into the calling thread
        Returns:
        a propagator that uses the given objects to propagate context

      • forTlsRemoveAfterTask

        static <T> ContextPropagator<T> forTlsRemoveAfterTask(ThreadLocal<T> threadLocal)
        Creates a ContextPropagator that propagates the value of the given thread-local variable, clearing thread-local state after each task. This differs from forTls(ThreadLocal) in that the restore step simply clears the value instead of restoring any previous value. Similarly, the install step of the returned propagator always returns null.
        Parameters:
        threadLocal - the thread-local variable whose value is propagated
        Returns:
        a propagator that propagates the value of the given thread-local variable, but clears it on finish instead of trying to restore a prior value
